00:00:14.680 --> 00:00:18.480
Potato croquettes with ham, appetizer as an ideal use.

00:00:20.980 --> 00:00:30.240
INGREDIENTS
2 large potatoes
50g chopped serrano ham
1/2 onion, chopped
Eggs
Flour
Bread crumbs
Olive oil
salt

00:00:32.360 --> 00:00:39.640
1. Boil the potatoes 20 minutes, cut and peeled.

00:00:41.100 --> 00:00:47.200
2. In a skillet lightly gilded onion.

00:00:49.480 --> 00:00:56.620
3. Add the ham onion and brown them all together.

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:02.140
4. Crush the cooked potato.

00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:09.000
5. Add the onion and ham to the potatoes and mix well.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:14.300
6. Let cool and form balls.

00:01:15.560 --> 00:01:31.240
7. spent the balls in flour, egg and bread crumbs.

00:01:40.940 --> 00:01:50.540
8. fry in olive oil until golden take them.

00:01:52.540 --> 00:01:54.540
We'll have the lists croquettes.

00:01:54.940 --> 00:01:56.940
Remember that cooking can be fun, bye !!!

